      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "\nJosé Carlos “Pepe” Luciano Huapaya was an Afro-Peruvian sociologist, academic, scholar, intellectual, and activist who fought for the recognition of Human Rights for Afro-Peruvian communities. His academic work was also tied to his political and cultural organizing in the Afro-Peruvian movements. His work was important because it analyzed the structural inequalities that shaped Blackness in the nation's history. \n"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "url": "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "\n"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "In 1980, he started working at the Instituto de Investigaciones Afroperuanas (INAPE), or in English, the Afro-Peruvian Research Institute, with another scholar named Jose \"Cheche\" Campos Davila. In this space, both scholars contributed to research, discussion, and political engagement around Afro-Peruvian life. Luciano’s involvement helped shape this space as one committed to producing knowledge from within Afro-Peruvian experiences and struggles.\n"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "His book "
        },
        {
          "text": "Los afroperuanos: Racismo, discriminación e identidad, ",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "or in English \"The Afro-Peruvians: Racism, discrimination and identity,\" is a foundational text for understanding how racism has been historically produced and sustained in Peru, as well as how Afro-Peruvians have constructed identity under those conditions. Combining sociological analysis with historical reflection and lived experience, the book shows that racism is not an individual issue but a structural system embedded in Peruvian society. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
